task.summary: Default task
updated method calls to reflect changes in ui class
Created logic package to handle calculations needed for graphing
Created object Champion to encapsulate associated data
created Type Map to encapsulate associated data
added variable skillRatingChange to represent the gain or loss of skill rating resulting from the game
renamed package gamesession -> gameround for consistency
added types Map and Champion as List's to logic component
added new types: logic, map, champions
initializeReader() now returns void instead of ExcelReader
added getters and setters
added getters and setters
made use of new types Map and Champion in parser moved initialization of Map and Champion temporarily to ExcelReader
GameRound now makes use of the new types Map and Champion
moved initialization of Map and Champion out of ui
Moved Maps and Champions initializations out of ExcelReader. Changed maps&champions from List to Set
Map initialization is now being done in its own Maps class
Champion initialization is now being done in its own ChampionRoster class.
Changed maps/champions from List to Set.
updated package name in imports
Changed method name to better explain what is happening in the method.
Updated method calls to reflect changes in ExcelReader, Maps, ChampionRoster.
Added champion "Other" to parser, whereas before championed remained null if not in set
changed implementation of calculateTotalWinRate, added comments.
added new fields to Champion. Champions now know: Their own total win rate, The different maps they can go to, their win rate on a per map basis(soon tm).
changed champion type mix to other to be consistent across other classes. Put Champion initializations into method. added getters and setters
removed load data button, as data is already being loaded on program start
split method calls in initialize() to class specific methods and added comments.
new method added, calculates win rate on a per map basis.
added if statement to prevent division by zero in cases where a champion had no games played
added method call to calculateWinRatePerMap() and some style changes
added test class for logic unit
Fixed 2 bugs in calculateTotalWinRates(Champion c): 1: Integer division was returning 0. 2: Division was being done in wrong order
made constructor public

Revert "Fixed 2 bugs in calculateTotalWinRates(Champion c): 1: Integer division was returning 0. 2: Division was being done in wrong order"
This reverts commit 192a67a
Fixed bugs: cast to double to prevent method from returning 0(by doing int division). made public to allow test to access
removed fields and added params to methods. this prevents duplication of the data where every class holds its own copy of the same data. also allows for tests to provide their own data when testing.
renamed methods and variable to be more clear about what they do.
moved initialization of gameRounds
added test for Logic.calculateWinRatePerMap()
overloaded constructor to make object creation more succinct
implemented new constructor in test case creation
added test for calculateWinRateEachMapAllChampions()
implemented barchart Hero win rate over map
removed VBox as it was not adding additional functionality
added method to call generateBarChart

factored out chart constructors and added button for barchart. changed charts to be generated and displayed on demand. instead of previously where they where being generated on startup and sitting idle in memory until user called the method.
code style cleanup
